Guildhouse
The Necromancers do not have a traditional ~>guildhouse<~. You will find
that it is actually one of ~>Alarian<~'s first crypts, before he and his
followers discovered his power over death. This tomb has long been sealed
off to the world, and buried under a millennia worth of soil and stone.
Alarian shaped the tomb with his magic to provide a shelter to both
himself and his followers. Now, the ~>guildhouse<~ acts as a hub of death
energy, providing Necromancers with several benefits. Here, they may
advance their studies in the dark arts, as well as spend their worldly
experience to better their body, mind, and soul. Additionally, a
Necromancer will notice that the guild hall is capable of creating a
personal crypt for them. Finally, the tomb is magically tied into a series
of collapsed graves, and will allow the Necromancer to quickly travel to
these locations. Since the tomb is sealed, a Necromancer must use the
~>nentomb<~ spell to return.
